Simulate responses

Bernardo Niebuhr

Simulate a landscape

First we simulate a landscape, using point-type infrastructure as an example.

library(mobsim)
library(raster)
## Loading required package: sp
library(ZOItools)

set.seed(1234)

# multiple focii
ext <- 30000
wd <- 0.1*ext
scales <- c(250, 500, 1000, 2500, 5000)/2
rasts <- simulate_dist_dens(n_features = 1000, centers = 5,
                            width = wd, res = 100,
                            extent_x = c(0, ext), extent_y = c(0, ext),
                            buffer_around = 10000,
                            type_density = "Gauss", scale = scales,
                            extent_x_cut = c(0, ext), extent_y_cut = c(0, ext))
plot(rasts)

Create a response

Now we wish to simulate a response using this landscape. We’ll consider a logistic response in the format

\[\begin{align*} y_i \sim {\sf Binom}(p_i) \\ logit(p_i) = log \left( \frac{p_1}{1 - p_i} \right) = \beta_{0i} + \beta_1 \cdot x_{1i} + \beta_2 \cdot x_{2i} \end{align*}\]

where \(y_i\) is the response variable (1 = used and 0 = available in the context of habitat suitability modeling), \(x_{1i}\) is a first variable independent from the space (added here just to consider one other factor of influence on the output), \(x_{2i}\) is either the density of features or the distance to the nearest feature, and \(\beta_0\), \(\beta_1\), and \(\beta_2\) are the coefficients of the equation.
